    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-04T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-04T00:35:00-05:00" n="383"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/737: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-04T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >March 4, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>156. Reference Department’s 71, February 10. British have submitted draft railway
                    financial agreement for consideration by Soviet Embassy and this office.
                    Substance of draft appears satisfactory to PGC and to me after careful study.
                    Text will be forwarded by air pouch leaving March 8.<note n="47"
                        xml:id="d383fn47">Text of draft agreement was transmitted to the Department
                        in despatch 869, March 7, from Tehran.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
